        <span class="tag tag-dim" style="margin-bottom:16px;display:inline-flex;">// about the kit</span>
        <h2 id="about-h">The complete Shopify automation kit — <span style="color:var(--g)">explained</span></h2>
        <p>Everything you need to know about what the Complete Kit is, how it works, and why it replaces $700+/month of paid apps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="seo-prose" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Article">
        <meta itemprop="headline" content="Stack Architect Complete Kit — Shopify Automation JSON Blueprint Files for Make.com">

        <h3>What is the Stack Architect Complete Kit?</h3>
        <p>The Stack Architect Complete Kit is a $49 one-time purchase that gives Shopify store owners four ready-to-import Make.com automation scenario files — pre-configured JSON blueprints that deploy server-side tracking, TikTok Events API, inventory management, and live profit reporting in under 10 minutes. The kit includes two Google Sheets templates and four Loom walkthrough videos. It replaces over $700 per month of paid Shopify apps including Elevar, Triple Whale, WeltPixel, Shopify Stocky, and TrueProfit.</p>

        <h3>What is a Make.com JSON blueprint and why does it matter?</h3>
        <p>A <strong>Make.com JSON blueprint</strong> (also called a scenario file) is a complete export of a finished Make.com automation. Every module, API endpoint, field mapping, routing rule, and connection setting is embedded inside the JSON file. Importing this file into Make.com recreates the entire automation in one click — no manual configuration required. This is different from a guide or tutorial, which describes how to build the automation step by step. The Complete Kit gives you the finished blueprint files, not the instructions for building them.</p>

        <h3>How does CAPI Shield replace Elevar and Triple Whale?</h3>
        <p>CAPI Shield is a Make.com automation scenario that routes Shopify order data server-to-server to <strong>Meta Conversions API</strong> and <strong>Google Enhanced Conversions</strong> simultaneously. Because the signal travels server-to-server rather than browser-to-pixel, iOS restrictions, ad blockers, and cookie expiry cannot intercept it. Stores typically recover 20–40% of conversion data that was previously invisible to their ad platforms after deploying CAPI Shield. <a href="/capi-shield">Elevar charges $150+ per month</a> for the same server-side tracking infrastructure. The CAPI Shield JSON blueprint achieves identical EMQ scores (7–8.5) at $0 per month after a $49 one-time kit purchase.</p>

        <h3>What is Stocky Swap and why is the August 2026 deadline important?</h3>
        <p>Stocky Swap is the inventory management scenario in the Complete Kit. It replicates Shopify Stocky's core function — logging every order in real time to a Google Sheets inventory dashboard with stock levels, fulfilment status, and order history. <strong>Shopify is permanently closing Stocky on August 31, 2026 and will delete all data after that date.</strong> Stocky Swap imports in under 60 seconds and begins capturing data immediately, requiring no manual data migration. It replaces paid inventory management tools including Linnworks and Skubana at $0 per month after the one-time kit purchase.</p>

        <h3>How does the TikTok CAPI scenario work for Shopify?</h3>
        <p>The TikTok CAPI scenario in the Complete Kit uses a Shopify order webhook to POST a <strong>CompletePayment event</strong> to the TikTok Events API server-to-server via Make.com. TikTok's server-side Events API accepts purchase events directly without relying on the browser-based TikTok Pixel. iOS Intelligent Tracking Prevention and ad blockers cannot intercept server-to-server signals. Most deployments achieve EMQ (Event Match Quality) scores of 6–8 in TikTok Events Manager. WeltPixel charges $39+ per month for TikTok server-side tracking. Analyzify charges $99+ per month. The Complete Kit achieves the same EMQ outcome at $0 per month.</p>

        <h3>How does P&L Auto replace TrueProfit?</h3>
        <p>P&L Auto is a Make.com scenario that fires the instant a Shopify order is paid. It extracts order value, product COGS, Shopify fees, and ad spend data and writes it to a pre-configured Google Sheets P&L dashboard automatically. Every order is accounted for in real time — no manual CSV exports, no end-of-month reconciliation, no BI tool subscription. TrueProfit charges $19–$99 per month for live Shopify profit reporting. BeProfit charges $29–$299 per month. The P&L Auto scenario in the Complete Kit produces a functionally equivalent live P&L dashboard at $0 per month.</p>

        <h3>Does the Complete Kit work for Shopify stores outside the US?</h3>
        <p>Yes. <strong>All four scenarios work globally.</strong> Shopify webhooks, Make.com, Meta Conversions API, Google Enhanced Conversions, and TikTok Events API all support international markets. The P&L Auto scenario supports any currency Shopify supports. Stores in the UK, EU, Australia, Canada, and all other Shopify markets are fully compatible. There are no geographic restrictions on the kit or any of the platforms it uses.</p>

        <h3>What is the difference between the Complete Kit and the free Stack Architect guides?</h3>
        <p>The <a href="/shopify-automation-guides">free Stack Architect guides</a> are step-by-step instructions for building each Make.com automation from scratch. Following them produces the same technical outcome as the Complete Kit — the same EMQ scores, the same attribution accuracy, the same inventory tracking, the same P&L data. The difference is time. Each guide takes approximately 2 hours to follow correctly. All four together take 8–10 hours. The Complete Kit gives you the finished JSON blueprint files that import in one click — total deployment time is 10 minutes. At $49, the kit costs less than an hour of most store owners' time.</p>
